11638
11639static bfd_boolean
11640elf_parse_notes (bfd *abfd, char *buf, size_t size, file_ptr offset,
11641 size_t align)
11642{
11643 char *p;
11644
11645 /* NB: CORE PT_NOTE segments may have p_align values of 0 or 1.
11646 gABI specifies that PT_NOTE alignment should be aligned to 4
11647 bytes for 32-bit objects and to 8 bytes for 64-bit objects. If
11648 align is less than 4, we use 4 byte alignment. */
11649 if (align < 4)
11650 align = 4;
11651 if (align != 4 && align != 8)
11652 return FALSE;
11653
11654 p = buf;
11655 while (p < buf + size)
11656 {
11657 Elf_External_Note *xnp = (Elf_External_Note *) p;
11658 Elf_Internal_Note in;
11659
11660 if (offsetof (Elf_External_Note, name) > buf - p + size)
11661 return FALSE;
11662
11663 in.type = H_GET_32 (abfd, xnp->type);
11664
11665 in.namesz = H_GET_32 (abfd, xnp->namesz);
11666 in.namedata = xnp->name;
11667 if (in.namesz > buf - in.namedata + size)
11668 return FALSE;
11669
11670 in.descsz = H_GET_32 (abfd, xnp->descsz);
11671 in.descdata = p + ELF_NOTE_DESC_OFFSET (in.namesz, align);
11672 in.descpos = offset + (in.descdata - buf);
11673 if (in.descsz != 0
11674 && (in.descdata >= buf + size
11675 || in.descsz > buf - in.descdata + size))
11676 return FALSE;
11677
11678 switch (bfd_get_format (abfd))
11679 {
11680 default:
11681 return TRUE;
11682
11683 case bfd_core:
11684 {
11685#define GROKER_ELEMENT(S,F) {S, sizeof (S) - 1, F}
11686 struct
11687 {
11688 const char * string;
11689 size_t len;
11690 bfd_boolean (* func)(bfd *, Elf_Internal_Note *);
11691 }
11692 grokers[] =
11693 {
11694 GROKER_ELEMENT ("", elfcore_grok_note),
11695 GROKER_ELEMENT ("FreeBSD", elfcore_grok_freebsd_note),
11696 GROKER_ELEMENT ("NetBSD-CORE", elfcore_grok_netbsd_note),
11697 GROKER_ELEMENT ( "OpenBSD", elfcore_grok_openbsd_note),
11698 GROKER_ELEMENT ("QNX", elfcore_grok_nto_note),
11699 GROKER_ELEMENT ("SPU/", elfcore_grok_spu_note)
11700 };
11701#undef GROKER_ELEMENT
11702 int i;
11703
11704 for (i = ARRAY_SIZE (grokers); i--;)
11705 {
11706 if (in.namesz >= grokers[i].len
11707 && strncmp (in.namedata, grokers[i].string,
11708 grokers[i].len) == 0)
11709 {
11710 if (! grokers[i].func (abfd, & in))
11711 return FALSE;
11712 break;
11713 }
11714 }
11715 break;
11716 }
11717
11718 case bfd_object:
11719 if (in.namesz == sizeof "GNU" && strcmp (in.namedata, "GNU") == 0)
11720 {
11721 if (! elfobj_grok_gnu_note (abfd, &in))
11722 return FALSE;
11723 }
11724 else if (in.namesz == sizeof "stapsdt"
11725 && strcmp (in.namedata, "stapsdt") == 0)
11726 {
11727 if (! elfobj_grok_stapsdt_note (abfd, &in))
11728 return FALSE;
11729 }
11730 break;
11731 }
11732
11733 p += ELF_NOTE_NEXT_OFFSET (in.namesz, in.descsz, align);
11734 }
11735
11736 return TRUE;
11737}
11738
11739static bfd_boolean
11740elf_read_notes (bfd *abfd, file_ptr offset, bfd_size_type size,
11741 size_t align)
11742{
11743 char *buf;
11744
11745 if (size == 0 || (size + 1) == 0)
11746 return TRUE;
11747
11748 if (bfd_seek (abfd, offset, SEEK_SET) != 0)
11749 return FALSE;
11750
11751 buf = (char *) bfd_malloc (size + 1);
11752 if (buf == NULL)
11753 return FALSE;
11754
11755 /* PR 17512: file: ec08f814
11756 0-termintate the buffer so that string searches will not overflow. */
11757 buf[size] = 0;
11758
11759 if (bfd_bread (buf, size, abfd) != size
11760 || !elf_parse_notes (abfd, buf, size, offset, align))
11761 {
11762 free (buf);
11763 return FALSE;
11764 }
11765
11766 free (buf);
11767 return TRUE;
11768}
11769
11770/* Providing external access to the ELF program header table. */
11771
11772/* Return an upper bound on the number of bytes required to store a
11773 copy of ABFD's program header table entries. Return -1 if an error
11774 occurs; bfd_get_error will return an appropriate code. */
11775
11776long
11777bfd_get_elf_phdr_upper_bound (bfd *abfd)
11778{
11779 if (abfd->xvec->flavour != bfd_target_elf_flavour)
11780 {
11781 bfd_set_error (bfd_error_wrong_format);
11782 return -1;
11783 }
11784
11785 return elf_elfheader (abfd)->e_phnum * sizeof (Elf_Internal_Phdr);
11786}
11787
11788/* Copy ABFD's program header table entries to *PHDRS. The entries
11789 will be stored as an array of Elf_Internal_Phdr structures, as
11790 defined in include/elf/internal.h. To find out how large the
11791 buffer needs to be, call bfd_get_elf_phdr_upper_bound.
11792
11793 Return the number of program header table entries read, or -1 if an
11794 error occurs; bfd_get_error will return an appropriate code. */
11795
11796int
11797bfd_get_elf_phdrs (bfd *abfd, void *phdrs)
11798{
11799 int num_phdrs;
11800
11801 if (abfd->xvec->flavour != bfd_target_elf_flavour)
11802 {
11803 bfd_set_error (bfd_error_wrong_format);
11804 return -1;
11805 }
11806
11807 num_phdrs = elf_elfheader (abfd)->e_phnum;
11808 if (num_phdrs != 0)
11809 memcpy (phdrs, elf_tdata (abfd)->phdr,
11810 num_phdrs * sizeof (Elf_Internal_Phdr));
11811
11812 return num_phdrs;
11813}
11814
11815enum elf_reloc_type_class
11816_bfd_elf_reloc_type_class (const struct bfd_link_info *info ATTRIBUTE_UNUSED,
11817 const asection *rel_sec ATTRIBUTE_UNUSED,
11818 const Elf_Internal_Rela *rela ATTRIBUTE_UNUSED)
11819{
11820 return reloc_class_normal;
11821}
11822
11823/* For RELA architectures, return the relocation value for a
11824 relocation against a local symbol. */
11825
11826bfd_vma
11827_bfd_elf_rela_local_sym (bfd *abfd,
11828 Elf_Internal_Sym *sym,
11829 asection **psec,
11830 Elf_Internal_Rela *rel)
11831{
11832 asection *sec = *psec;
11833 bfd_vma relocation;
11834
11835 relocation = (sec->output_section->vma
11836 + sec->output_offset
11837 + sym->st_value);
11838 if ((sec->flags & SEC_MERGE)
11839 && ELF_ST_TYPE (sym->st_info) == STT_SECTION
11840 && sec->sec_info_type == SEC_INFO_TYPE_MERGE)
11841 {
11842 rel->r_addend =
11843 _bfd_merged_section_offset (abfd, psec,
11844 elf_section_data (sec)->sec_info,
11845 sym->st_value + rel->r_addend);
11846 if (sec != *psec)
11847 {
11848 /* If we have changed the section, and our original section is
11849 marked with SEC_EXCLUDE, it means that the original
11850 SEC_MERGE section has been completely subsumed in some
11851 other SEC_MERGE section. In this case, we need to leave
11852 some info around for --emit-relocs. */
11853 if ((sec->flags & SEC_EXCLUDE) != 0)
11854 sec->kept_section = *psec;
11855 sec = *psec;
11856 }
11857 rel->r_addend -= relocation;
11858 rel->r_addend += sec->output_section->vma + sec->output_offset;
11859 }
11860 return relocation;
11861}
11862
11863bfd_vma
11864_bfd_elf_rel_local_sym (bfd *abfd,
11865 Elf_Internal_Sym *sym,
11866 asection **psec,
11867 bfd_vma addend)
11868{
11869 asection *sec = *psec;
11870
11871 if (sec->sec_info_type != SEC_INFO_TYPE_MERGE)
11872 return sym->st_value + addend;
11873
11874 return _bfd_merged_section_offset (abfd, psec,
11875 elf_section_data (sec)->sec_info,
11876 sym->st_value + addend);
11877}
11878
11879/* Adjust an address within a section. Given OFFSET within SEC, return
11880 the new offset within the section, based upon changes made to the
11881 section. Returns -1 if the offset is now invalid.
11882 The offset (in abnd out) is in target sized bytes, however big a
11883 byte may be. */
11884
11885bfd_vma
11886_bfd_elf_section_offset (bfd *abfd,
11887 struct bfd_link_info *info,
11888 asection *sec,
11889 bfd_vma offset)
11890{
11891 switch (sec->sec_info_type)
11892 {
11893 case SEC_INFO_TYPE_STABS:
11894 return _bfd_stab_section_offset (sec, elf_section_data (sec)->sec_info,
11895 offset);
11896 case SEC_INFO_TYPE_EH_FRAME:
11897 return _bfd_elf_eh_frame_section_offset (abfd, info, sec, offset);
11898
11899 default:
11900 if ((sec->flags & SEC_ELF_REVERSE_COPY) != 0)
11901 {
11902 /* Reverse the offset. */
11903 const struct elf_backend_data *bed = get_elf_backend_data (abfd);
11904 bfd_size_type address_size = bed->s->arch_size / 8;
11905
11906 /* address_size and sec->size are in octets. Convert
11907 to bytes before subtracting the original offset. */
11908 offset = (sec->size - address_size) / bfd_octets_per_byte (abfd) - offset;
11909 }
11910 return offset;
11911 }
11912}
11913
11914/* Create a new BFD as if by bfd_openr. Rather than opening a file,
11915 reconstruct an ELF file by reading the segments out of remote memory
11916 based on the ELF file header at EHDR_VMA and the ELF program headers it
11917 points to. If not null, *LOADBASEP is filled in with the difference
11918 between the VMAs from which the segments were read, and the VMAs the
11919 file headers (and hence BFD's idea of each section's VMA) put them at.
11920
11921 The function TARGET_READ_MEMORY is called to copy LEN bytes from the
11922 remote memory at target address VMA into the local buffer at MYADDR; it
11923 should return zero on success or an `errno' code on failure. TEMPL must
11924 be a BFD for an ELF target with the word size and byte order found in
11925 the remote memory. */
11926
11927bfd *
11928bfd_elf_bfd_from_remote_memory
11929 (bfd *templ,
11930 bfd_vma ehdr_vma,
11931 bfd_size_type size,
11932 bfd_vma *loadbasep,
11933 int (*target_read_memory) (bfd_vma, bfd_byte *, bfd_size_type))
11934{
11935 return (*get_elf_backend_data (templ)->elf_backend_bfd_from_remote_memory)
11936 (templ, ehdr_vma, size, loadbasep, target_read_memory);
11937}
11938
11939long
11940_bfd_elf_get_synthetic_symtab (bfd *abfd,
11941 long symcount ATTRIBUTE_UNUSED,
11942 asymbol **syms ATTRIBUTE_UNUSED,
11943 long dynsymcount,
11944 asymbol **dynsyms,
11945 asymbol **ret)
11946{
11947 const struct elf_backend_data *bed = get_elf_backend_data (abfd);
11948 asection *relplt;
11949 asymbol *s;
11950 const char *relplt_name;
11951 bfd_boolean (*slurp_relocs) (bfd *, asection *, asymbol **, bfd_boolean);
11952 arelent *p;
11953 long count, i, n;
11954 size_t size;
11955 Elf_Internal_Shdr *hdr;
11956 char *names;
11957 asection *plt;
11958
11959 *ret = NULL;
11960
11961 if ((abfd->flags & (DYNAMIC | EXEC_P)) == 0)
11962 return 0;
11963
11964 if (dynsymcount <= 0)
11965 return 0;
11966
11967 if (!bed->plt_sym_val)
11968 return 0;
11969
11970 relplt_name = bed->relplt_name;
11971 if (relplt_name == NULL)
11972 relplt_name = bed->rela_plts_and_copies_p ? ".rela.plt" : ".rel.plt";
11973 relplt = bfd_get_section_by_name (abfd, relplt_name);
11974 if (relplt == NULL)
11975 return 0;
11976
11977 hdr = &elf_section_data (relplt)->this_hdr;
11978 if (hdr->sh_link != elf_dynsymtab (abfd)
11979 || (hdr->sh_type != SHT_REL && hdr->sh_type != SHT_RELA))
11980 return 0;
11981
11982 plt = bfd_get_section_by_name (abfd, ".plt");
11983 if (plt == NULL)
11984 return 0;
11985
11986 slurp_relocs = get_elf_backend_data (abfd)->s->slurp_reloc_table;
11987 if (! (*slurp_relocs) (abfd, relplt, dynsyms, TRUE))
11988 return -1;
11989
11990 count = relplt->size / hdr->sh_entsize;
11991 size = count * sizeof (asymbol);
11992 p = relplt->relocation;
11993 for (i = 0; i < count; i++, p += bed->s->int_rels_per_ext_rel)
11994 {
11995 size += strlen ((*p->sym_ptr_ptr)->name) + sizeof ("@plt");
11996 if (p->addend != 0)
11997 {
11998#ifdef BFD64
11999 size += sizeof ("+0x") - 1 + 8 + 8 * (bed->s->elfclass == ELFCLASS64);
12000#else
12001 size += sizeof ("+0x") - 1 + 8;
12002#endif
12003 }
12004 }
12005
12006 s = *ret = (asymbol *) bfd_malloc (size);
12007 if (s == NULL)
12008 return -1;
12009
12010 names = (char *) (s + count);
12011 p = relplt->relocation;
12012 n = 0;
12013 for (i = 0; i < count; i++, p += bed->s->int_rels_per_ext_rel)
12014 {
12015 size_t len;
12016 bfd_vma addr;
12017
12018 addr = bed->plt_sym_val (i, plt, p);
12019 if (addr == (bfd_vma) -1)
12020 continue;
12021
12022 *s = **p->sym_ptr_ptr;
12023 /* Undefined syms won't have BSF_LOCAL or BSF_GLOBAL set. Since
12024 we are defining a symbol, ensure one of them is set. */
12025 if ((s->flags & BSF_LOCAL) == 0)
12026 s->flags |= BSF_GLOBAL;
12027 s->flags |= BSF_SYNTHETIC;
12028 s->section = plt;
12029 s->value = addr - plt->vma;
12030 s->name = names;
12031 s->udata.p = NULL;
12032 len = strlen ((*p->sym_ptr_ptr)->name);
12033 memcpy (names, (*p->sym_ptr_ptr)->name, len);
12034 names += len;
12035 if (p->addend != 0)
12036 {
12037 char buf[30], *a;
12038
12039 memcpy (names, "+0x", sizeof ("+0x") - 1);
12040 names += sizeof ("+0x") - 1;
12041 bfd_sprintf_vma (abfd, buf, p->addend);
12042 for (a = buf; *a == '0'; ++a)
12043 ;
12044 len = strlen (a);
12045 memcpy (names, a, len);
12046 names += len;
12047 }
12048 memcpy (names, "@plt", sizeof ("@plt"));
12049 names += sizeof ("@plt");
12050 ++s, ++n;
12051 }
12052
12053 return n;
12054}
12055
12056/* It is only used by x86-64 so far.
12057 ??? This repeats *COM* id of zero. sec->id is supposed to be unique,
12058 but current usage would allow all of _bfd_std_section to be zero. */
12059static const asymbol lcomm_sym
12060 = GLOBAL_SYM_INIT ("LARGE_COMMON", &_bfd_elf_large_com_section);
12061asection _bfd_elf_large_com_section
12062 = BFD_FAKE_SECTION (_bfd_elf_large_com_section, &lcomm_sym,
12063 "LARGE_COMMON", 0, SEC_IS_COMMON);
12064
12065void
12066_bfd_elf_post_process_headers (bfd * abfd,
12067 struct bfd_link_info * link_info ATTRIBUTE_UNUSED)
12068{
12069 Elf_Internal_Ehdr * i_ehdrp; /* ELF file header, internal form. */
12070
12071 i_ehdrp = elf_elfheader (abfd);
12072
12073 i_ehdrp->e_ident[EI_OSABI] = get_elf_backend_data (abfd)->elf_osabi;
12074
12075 /* To make things simpler for the loader on Linux systems we set the
12076 osabi field to ELFOSABI_GNU if the binary contains symbols of
12077 the STT_GNU_IFUNC type or STB_GNU_UNIQUE binding. */
12078 if (i_ehdrp->e_ident[EI_OSABI] == ELFOSABI_NONE
12079 && elf_tdata (abfd)->has_gnu_symbols)
12080 i_ehdrp->e_ident[EI_OSABI] = ELFOSABI_GNU;
12081}
12082
12083
12084/* Return TRUE for ELF symbol types that represent functions.
12085 This is the default version of this function, which is sufficient for
12086 most targets. It returns true if TYPE is STT_FUNC or STT_GNU_IFUNC. */
12087
12088bfd_boolean
12089_bfd_elf_is_function_type (unsigned int type)
12090{
12091 return (type == STT_FUNC
12092 || type == STT_GNU_IFUNC);
12093}
12094
12095/* If the ELF symbol SYM might be a function in SEC, return the
12096 function size and set *CODE_OFF to the function's entry point,
12097 otherwise return zero. */
12098
12099bfd_size_type
12100_bfd_elf_maybe_function_sym (const asymbol *sym, asection *sec,
12101 bfd_vma *code_off)
12102{
12103 bfd_size_type size;
12104
12105 if ((sym->flags & (BSF_SECTION_SYM | BSF_FILE | BSF_OBJECT
12106 | BSF_THREAD_LOCAL | BSF_RELC | BSF_SRELC)) != 0
12107 || sym->section != sec)
12108 return 0;
12109
12110 *code_off = sym->value;
12111 size = 0;
12112 if (!(sym->flags & BSF_SYNTHETIC))
12113 size = ((elf_symbol_type *) sym)->internal_elf_sym.st_size;
12114 if (size == 0)
12115 size = 1;
12116 return size;
12117}
